title: Rain postpones tennis Regionals
text:
Rain postpones tennis Regionals The rain Saturday forced the postponement of the Northern Nevada Division I and I-A Regional tennis tournaments. The rain Saturday forced the postponement of the Northern Nevada Division I and I-A Regional tennis tournaments. 
All Division I rounds are postponed until noon Monday at the Caughlin Athletic Club in Reno. 
In the Division I semifinals, Reno’s top-seed McKenna LeVitt will face Spanish Springs’ Lauren Kreutzer at noon and Madelyn Landerfelt of Douglas will face Brittany Leonard of Bishop Manogue. 
In the Div. I boys semifinal, top-seed Tim Zagar of Damonte Ranch will face C.J. Hess of Galena at noon, and Zeke Brooke of Damonte will play Natale Castelli, also of Damonte. 
The Division I-A semifinals will begin at 10 a.m. Monday at the Reno Tennis Center — Plumas Courts for the resumption of the quarterfinals. 
Donnie Nelson, assistant director of the Nevada Athletic Activities Association, said all schedule options were considered, taking into account court availability, loss of school time and state travel plans. Read or Share this story: http://on.rgj.com/1ROCu2u TOP VIDEOS
